Tempers are flaring in Eldorado Park, Johannesburg. Some areas have been without electricity for weeks. In Extension 1, the lights have been off for 6 weeks and the community has had enough. It's threatening to shut roads. eNCA's Aviwe Mtila has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Tempers are flaring in Eldorado Park, Johannesburg. Some areas have been without electricity for weeks. READ: Soweto residents continue protest over electricity In Extension 1, the lights have been off for 6 weeks and the community has had enough. It's threatening to shut roads. City Power says it is increasing capacity at the Eldorado Park substation. eNCA’s Aviwe Mtila shares more details in the video above.